SUMMARY:NJ Audubon: Primer for Spring Birding at Hawk Rise
DESCRIPTION:Led by Angus Macaulay\, NJ Audubon Teacher Naturalist \nSpring will bring some of the best birding of the year. Now is the time to get ready! Join us at Hawk Rise for a birding walk along the trails of Hawk Rise\, and a discussion of the resources available to birders. We will touch on binoculars\, phone apps\, and prime locations. Loaner binoculars will be available. This program is appropriate for individuals of all ages. Come dressed for the weather. Hot or cold beverages will be served afterwards depending on the weather. \nCOST: FREE \nInterested in becoming an NJ Audubon member? Please click on the following link to learn more or join: Become a Member today! \nCANCELLATION: NJA/CMBO programs require a minimum number of registrants to run\, five days in advance of the start of the tour but are seldom cancelled. If we do cancel\, due to lack of participation\, severe weather\, or unforeseen circumstances\, we notify all participants in advance\, and all are eligible for a full credit or refund. Participants may cancel without penalty if greater than 30 days in advance. Cancellations 10 to 30 days in advance may be subject to a 25% service charge. No refunds or credits for cancellations less than ten days in advance unless due to health emergencies. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/nj-audubon-primer-for-spring-birding-at-hawk-rise/
LOCATION:Hawk Rise Sanctuary\, 1811 Lower Rd\, Linden\, NJ\, 07036\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bird Walk,Birding,Hawk Rise,Scherman Hoffman Wildlife Sanctuary
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://njaudubon.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Primer-for-Spring-Birding-at-Hawk-Rise-2026.jpg
GEO:40.6041342249;-74.252034991
