SUMMARY:Craft for the Birds!
DESCRIPTION:Craft a life-sized bird sculpture from upcycled cloth and become part of a crowdsourced art project! Join area writer\, birder\, and conservation advocate Kelly Ball to craft a life-sized bird sculpture from upcycled cloth and become part of a crowdsourced art project. Each handcrafted bird commemorates a real bird that lost its life after hitting glass. Your bird will become part of a 300-ft art project that will travel the U.S. to educate the public about bird-window collisions and you’ll be part of the searchable database of people that contributed. We’ll also learn how to prevent bird-window collisions – especially important during spring migration! \nNote: This is a family-friendly program. Adults must accompany children. Participation is limited. Pre-registration is required. \nWHERE: Nature Center of Cape May\, 1600 Delaware Avenue\, Cape May\, NJ. \nWHEN: Saturday\, March 7th\, 1pm-3pm \nCOST: This is a FREE workshop\, but we highly encourage a $5 donation to support the amazing work of the Nature Center of Cape May. \nInterested in becoming a member? Please click on the following link to learn more or join: Become a Member Today! \n\n\n\nCANCELLATION POLICY: NJ Audubon’s programs require a minimum number of registrants to run. If we cancel\, due to lack of participation\, severe weather\, or unforeseen circumstances\, all participants will be notified as soon as possible and are eligible for a full refund. Participants may cancel without penalty if greater than 48 hours in advance. Sorry\, no refund for cancellations less than 48 hours in advance unless due to health emergencies; however\, registrations can be transferred to another program in the future. \n\nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/craft-for-the-birds/
LOCATION:Nature Center of Cape May\, 1600 Delaware Avenue\, Cape May\, NJ\, 08204\, United States
CATEGORIES:Event,Family Program,Nature Center of Cape May
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://njaudubon.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Craft-for-the-Birds-03.2026.jpg
GEO:38.9452704878;-74.8992712451
